A message from our editor-in-chief, Amy Keller Laird: 
"On Wednesday, we wear red. Because that's what Women's Health  is about. Red. Strength. Empowerment. And not just on this Wednesday, when we're celebrating strong women around the world and throughout history. But every day. When I became EIC of this brand in 2014, we had an international conference coming up, and I was asked what our signature logo color was. The assumption was pink, since Men's Health (our older bro!) is red. No. Women's Health is red too. Our new April issue is a visual representation of this. And it's not because Gwyneth Paltrow is in a red swimsuit. It's because she's bold, she says what she thinks, she isn't afraid to try new things—and that's worth celebrating.
